modules.description: Converts strings between snake_case, camelCase, and PascalCase formats using case transformation functions. Operates on standard string values and applies pattern-based replacement rules. Useful for generating consistent identifier formats in code generation or data normalization tasks.

Provides functions to convert and compare string case conventions, including applying rules to snake_case strings and lists of words. Works with a custom type representing case styles such as camelCase, snake_case, and PascalCase. Used to standardize naming in code generation or user input validation.
